casebody.data:
Don Victor HARBOLT, Jr., Petitioner-Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Respondent-Appellee. No. 71-1762

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Sept. 10, 1971. Don Victor Harbolt, Jr., pro se. John L. Briggs, U. S. Atty., Bernard H. Dempsey, Jr., Asst. U. S. Atty., Tampa, Fla., for respondent-appellee.

Before GEWIN, GOLDBERG and DYER, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5th Cir. See Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Co. of New York et al., 5th Cir. 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part I.

 PER CURIAM:

Judgment affirmed. See United States v. Harbolt, 426 F.2d 1346 (5th Cir. 1970). See Local Rule 21.1

. See NLRB v. Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, 430 F.2d 966 (5th Cir. 1970).
